# useAxios Hook Usage

## Core Rules

- **Always use `useAxios` hook** from `@/hooks/useAxios` for all API calls
- **Never use direct API calls** in components (no `createApiClient` in components)
- **Create service layer** for all API endpoints in `*ApiService.ts` files

## File Structure

```
app/[feature]/_complex_components/services/[Feature]ApiService.ts
```

## Hook Pattern

```typescript
// Service file
export const useFetchResource = (id: string) => {
    return useAxios<ResourceDto>(`/resources/${id}`, {
        method: "GET"
    });
};
```

## Component Usage

### With Dynamic Parameters
```typescript
const { startFetch } = useCreateResource();

const handleSubmit = async (values: any) => {
    await startFetch({
        data: values
    });
};
```

## Type Safety

Always provide explicit TypeScript types:

```typescript
// Good
return useAxios<WorkflowDto[]>("/workflows", { method: "GET" });

// Bad - missing type
return useAxios("/workflows", { method: "GET" });
```

## Common Patterns

### Fetch on Mount
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
    startFetch();
}, [startFetch]);
```

### Polling
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
    const intervalId = setInterval(() => {
        startFetch();
    }, 2000);
    return () => clearInterval(intervalId);
}, [startFetch]);
```

### Handle Side Effects
```typescript
useEffect(() => {
    if (data?.id) {
        handleSuccess(data.id);
    }
}, [data]);

useEffect(() => {
    if (error) {
        handleError(error.message);
    }
}, [error]);
```

## Built-in Features (Automatic)

- Authentication token injection
- Loading state management
- Error handling (401, 403, 404, 429, 500)
- Request cancellation on unmount
- Compression for large payloads (>128KB)
- Analytics tracking for errors
- Retry logic for rate limits and server errors

## Constants

Define reusable endpoint values in constants:

```typescript
// constants/endpoint-constants.ts
export const EXECUTION_TRIGGERED_BY_INTERFACE = "interface";

// Usage in service
params: {
    executionTriggeredBy: EXECUTION_TRIGGERED_BY_INTERFACE
}
```

## Checklist for New API Endpoints

- [ ] Create service file in correct location
- [ ] Export hook with descriptive name
- [ ] Add explicit TypeScript types
- [ ] Use descriptive variable names when destructuring
- [ ] Handle loading, error, and success states
- [ ] Define constants for reusable values
